National Grid plc

National Grid House Warwick Technology Park, Gallows Hill
Warwick  CV34 6DA United Kingdom
Phone: +44 ____ ______
Fax: +44 ____ ______
http://www2.nationalgrid.com/uk





55
Managers




2072
IT employees




$792.5MEST.
IT Budget




Founded in 1990, National Grid plc and its subsidiaries transmit and distribute electricity and gas in the United Kingdom and the United States. In the UK, they own and operate high voltage electricity transmission networks, the electricity interconnector between England… MoreFounded in 1990, National Grid plc and its subsidiaries transmit and distribute electricity and gas in the United Kingdom and the United States. In the UK, they own and operate high voltage electricity transmission networks, the electricity interconnector between England and France, liquefied natural gas storage facilities, and four gas distribution networks. Its Non-Regulated and Other businesses division's UK operations include metering services, property management, a liquefied natural gas (LNG) importation terminal on the Isle of Grain, and the construction and operation of an electricity interconnector between the Netherlands and the United Kingdom.

Procurement Process:
IT Sourcing is managed through the company's procurement department.
2013 and previously:

Founded in 1990, National Grid plc and its subsidiaries transmit and distribute electricity and gas in the United Kingdom and the United States. In the UK, they own and operate high voltage electricity transmission networks, the electricity interconnector… More2013 and previously:

Founded in 1990, National Grid plc and its subsidiaries transmit and distribute electricity and gas in the United Kingdom and the United States. In the UK, they own and operate high voltage electricity transmission networks, the electricity interconnector between England and France, liquefied natural gas storage facilities, and four gas distribution networks.

Its Non-Regulated and Other businesses division's UK operations include metering services, property management, a liquefied natural gas (LNG) importation terminal on the Isle of Grain, and the construction and operation of an electricity interconnector between the Netherlands and the United Kingdom.

IT operations are run by a Global CIO out of IT headquarters in Warwick, UK. IT's primary focus is on monitoring the distribution and pricing of both electricity and gas. 

Global managers and department heads report to the CIO and are responsible for Global Projects, Risk & Security, Strategy and Architecture, Global IT Corporate Business Relationships, Network Operations, and Network Strategy.

The Solihull office houses telecom management and IT managers focused on developing and implementing project strategies.

This office shares a building and a telephone switchboard with Xoserve, an independent Natural Grid spin-off corporation, which is the supply point administrator of Great Britain's open electricity market. OnStream, a wholly owned metering service subsidiary of National Grid, is also located here.

A large portion of IT management and support is outsourced to Computer Sciences Corporation. CSC works with National Grid's mainframes, applications, desktop, and telecommunication services supporting more than 18,000 National Grid users. National Grid's "internal" IT help desk is also run by CSC.

In April, 2011, National Grid plc signed a seven-year service agreement with HP Enterprise Services UK, in which HP will provide a solution that helps manage National Grid's hybrid technology environment and increase response rates to market changes. 

National Grid's US operations are profiled separately.

Dial 1 before all nine-digit telephone numbers.





